Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: The suite is located in 250 South Oak Way, positioned in the heart of Green Park office park. Internally the office has fully raised floors with a suspended ceiling and Cat II lighting. The office is currently fitted with open plan work stations (16 desks), 4 glazed offices, a board room and a kitchenette. 250 South Oak Way is a modern multi occupier building positioned at the heart of Green Park on Lime Square. Lime Square is the central amenity offering for Green Park and offers a range of facilities including Nuffield Health & Fitness club, Zest Bar & Brasserie, WH Smith.

Unit 150 is a self-contained office with mezzanine floor and meeting rooms. Unit 150 is set within an impressive landscaped environment and the Winnersh Triangle amenities and train station. Occupiers benefit from fantastic road connections, offering easy access to the M4.
Unit 135 is a first floor and mezzanine office set within a landscaped environment located on Wharfdale Road adjacent to Winnersh Triangle Train Station.
Unit 145 offers bright offices in a landscaped environment located immediately adjacent to Winnersh Triangle Train Station.

Building 1180 is part of a new generation of agile
business spaces at Winnersh Triangle encouraging
collaboration and shared ideas, geared towards
creative thinking, problem solving and innovation.
Located along the Eskdale Road, it is perfectly
situated on the park to give your wellbeing a boost,
immediately adjoining the brand-new sports and
wellness hub.


The building also houses a new state of the art cafe
with co-working space. Providing not only a perfect
cuppa or cappuccino but a vibrant atmosphere,
giving your team somewhere to relax or catch-up
out of the office.


1180 is an easy walk to Winnersh Triangle train station
and other onsite amenities; making it simple for you
to reconnect people with your business.

1010 is located within the central piazza opposite to the main amenity offer including the 4 star Holiday Inn, Gather and Gather café/bar, WHSmith convenience store and direct access to Winnersh Triangle railway station.

Unit 110 is a first floor office set within a landscaped environment located on Wharfdale Road adjacent to Winnersh Triangle Train Station. The Park has its own dedicated rail station, ‘Winnersh Triangle’, just a three minute walk from the Piazza, providing direct and frequent rail services to Central London and Reading, with trains running every 30 minutes.

1020 is located within the central piazza in very close proximity to the main amenity offer including the new 4 star Holiday Inn, Gather & Gather café/
bar, WH Smith convenience store and direct access to Winnersh Triangle railway station.

A contemporary, inspiring 62,000 sq ft newly refurbished office building available from September 2020. 31,000 sq ft has recently been let to Hewlett Packard Enterprise, leaving 31,000 sq ft available on the first floor.

Building 1000 is a first floor office set within an impressive landscaped environment with views over the green and the Winnersh Triangle amenities and
train station. Occupiers benefit from fantastic road connections, offering easy access to the M4.

Common.FloorPlans.Common.ImageCaption: NO2 FORBURY PLACE UPPER FLOOR PLAN

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Forbury Place’s prime location offers all the lifestyle benefits you’d expect, with high street retail, restaurants and bars, local heritage, and the relaxing green spaces of Forbury Gardens all within a short walk. Transport links are equally impressive with abundant car parking, easy connections to the motorway network, Reading Station a five-minute walk away and plenty of public transport nearby, it’s an impeccably well-connected development. Forbury Place is no ordinary office development. This landmark building combines striking architectural features with the flexible yet efficient use of floorspace that’s the hallmark of today’s most progressive office developments.  The stunning double-height reception provides a preview of the high quality finishes that extend throughout the building’s large floor plates.

No.3 Forbury Place offers high quality non-fitted office space on part of the 10th floor. Featuring an enhanced reception, external landscaping and a new eatery ‘Forbury Kitchen’ serving the wider Forbury Place Estate. Home to Yell, Pegasystems, Convatec, Osborne Clarke, PwC and BPP, the size and scale of this development is what you would expect of a prestigious Central London development. Designed on truly out-of-town scale it cements Reading’s position as a key business hub outside the Capital. The available accommodation has been refurbished in its entirety, along with an enhanced reception, landscaping and a ‘the Forbury kitchen’.

No.3 Forbury Place offers high quality fitted office space over parts of 1st floor. Featuring an enhanced reception, external landscaping and a new eatery ‘Forbury Kitchen’ serving the wider Forbury Place Estate. Home to Yell, Pegasystems, Convatec, Osborne Clarke, PwC and BPP, the size and scale of this development is what you would expect of a prestigious Central London development. Designed on truly out-of-town scale it cements Reading’s position as a key business hub outside the Capital. The available accommodation has been refurbished in its entirety, along with an enhanced reception, landscaping and a ‘the Forbury kitchen’.

Quadrant, situated on Windsor High Street is a contemporary 4 storey office building showcasing a full-heighted glazed atrium reception. The 8,862 sq. ft 1st floor space is home to an open-plan office with adjoining board room and lounge which is soon to be refurbished to CAT A standard, available for occupation at the end of Q2 2021.

Heathrow Approach has been refurbished to create a striking headquarters office building. The building is finished to the highest specification, boasting a stunning triple height reception area, Grade A office accommodation and new landscaped approach. In addition, a newly clad metal fin to the building’s exterior provides an innovative branding opportunity, enhancing the building’s profile and that of the occupier. The upper floors provide large uninterrupted open floor plates. The lower floors are connected by a central glazed walkway. At ground floor level the contemporary reception area creates a dramatic statement for any visitor. Heathrow Approach benefits from a very prominent position adjacent to junction 5 of the M4 which on average has 130,000 vehicles pass through it every day.

Prominently located in the heart of Slough, the UK’s most productive borough and voted best UK town to work in, The Porter Building sets the standard for connectivity as well as best in class Wellness, BREAAM and Wired Score certificates.

Directly facing Slough’s Elizabeth Line station, the building benefits from unrivalled connectivity. Trains to London Paddington take just 13 minutes with up to 14 trains per hour, a short 6 minute drive will provide access to J6 of the M4 and journeys to London Heathrow airport take only 17 minutes. 

Slough has one of the strongest economies in the UK, with many businesses including Fiat, Intel and Reckitt Benckiser choosing to set up their headquarters in the town. Slough also boasts a huge range of amenity including the Queensmere Shopping centre, Nando’s restaurant and Tesco extra, all of which are just a short walk from The Porter Building.

Horizon is a high quality office building set in the heart of the Thames Valley countryside. The building comprises a double height reception with an onsite café and gym on the ground floor. Surrounded by the Thames Valley countryside with over 11 acres of landscaped grounds, Horizon is located
just off the A404 between the M4 and M40 motorways.
